* M. Le Goc, LSIS, France, 'Learning with the Theory of Timed Observations'
* H. Glotin, LSIS & Inst. Univ. de France, 'Sparse Coding for Audio
Retrieval applied to Bioacoustics'

Registration deadline: 9th September, 2013 (CB / Invoice...) :
http://glotin.univ-tln.fr/ERMITES13

The ERMITES 2013 Summer School brings together international leading
researchers and provides participants the opportunity to gain deeper
insight into current research trends in scaled audiovisual information
retrieval. It is organized as a series of long talks, during which
students are invited to interact. The target audience of the school is
graduate and PhD students, post-doctoral researchers, academic and
industrial researchers as well as developers.

Org. (pres.) : J. Razik (org.), H. Glotin (prog.)

